node.text:
Had a great cardio session and wanted to share my thoughts with you all. 

I encourage you to give yourself permission to be your absolute best version of self! Create positive, relentless momentum in everything you do as you just might surprise yourself. Once you do this, your body, mind and spirit will give you some important certainty that you can use to achieve an even greater level of badassery! Fight the noise that limits yourself to be happy and go get yourself a victory today!!! 

Be strong, be confident, be your best your absolute best will always be good enough!

node.title: Setting the table for your own greatness!

node.text:
I truly wish everyone a great day and weekend, but most importantly I hope that you all stay encouraged no matter what the world is throwing at you. 

Remember, curve balls CAN be hit! You've just gotta stay in that batter's box, FOCUS and take a freakin SWING!!!

Love to ALL!

#philheath
#gratitude
#thankyou
#staystrong 
#staysafe
#betonyourself 
#triumph

node.text: It’s past midnight and I just got done training shoulders. I start my week on Sunday because I use that positive momentum as I go into Monday. I encourage you all to start this week with some positive momentum.. What are you grateful for? What are your goals this week? You can do anything you put your mind to, but you have to do the work! Let’s go! Let’s work! Happy Monday💪🏽

node.text: @iconmeals has saved us🙌🏽 We don’t stress anymore about getting meals in on time. Anyone who knows me personally, knows I can get by with 2 meals a day while getting caught up in work and conf calls. This never makes me feel great when I hit the gym later in the evening. @shuriecremona is also very busy with running @gifted_athletics and she’s currently prepping to get in her best shape👏 Fact is- When you fail to plan, you plan to fail. We created a bad habit of only staying on track with meals while I’m in prep. Prepping food is very time consuming and became very draining while managing my crazy schedule. Icon makes your order, flash freezes it and ships it to you immediately. This is why ours is still frozen and freshly cooked. I have included my code in my bio, we love Icon because their food is awesome, made to order and the owners are incredible people. Check them out and feel free to hit us up if you have any questions💪🏽 Code: MRO

node.text:
This post is about Seahawks Legend Ron Howard recounting some of his favorite memories as a member of the Seahawks. What is even more special is that Coach Howard was my middle school Gym Teacher and was also my High School Track and Assistant Basketball Coach for Rainier Beach 1995-1998. I have been blessed to know Coach Howard as he's been like a Father to me along with many other kids now Men. 
Listening to his champion mindset as Coach Howard also was Tight End for the Dallas Cowboys winning a Super Bowl Ring and actually seeing that ring made me believe that anything is possible with hard work, being a good listener and exhibiting a killer instinct toward my goals. I could go on and on about Coach Howard and will probably share more another time but until then enjoy the video as he is a true Legend in Football and even more for his commitment to educating youths in South End of Seattle. 

Love ya Coach Howard! Can't wait to link up with ya soon.

Thankful for it all, but most importantly I am truly grateful for this birthday to fall upon the Mr Olympia prejudging. I am ready to make my mark and tonight I bring forth a greater mind, body and spirit. The journey has always been filled with challenges and with everything that has transpired over the last two years, I'm ready to show just how much I have elevated in life. Thank you all for the messages and look forward to completing my mission starting tonight!

🎥 @originmediaco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Phil Heath on August 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, people kissing, ocean, beach, twilight and text that says '×1 shuriecremona'.

node.text:
When I say I am blessed, I truly am by the grace of God lemme tell ya. Honored and privileged to walk through this journey here on Earth with this incredibly awesome, passionate, intelligent, humble and gorgeous Woman! I love U #Repost @shuriecremona with @make_repost
・・・
I see a lot of people hashtag “Couple Goals” on our photos and I see much of that on photos of couples that are a week/month into their relationship. Instagram is a highlight reel of moments in time. Do you compare your relationship to other couples on IG? Do you really see our photos and feel like your relationship should be just like ours? Phil and I have been fairly open with our loyalty and respect for each other. We haven’t shared the many hard moments filled with Adversity, Pain, Struggle, Tears, Misunderstandings and Growing Pains. We might be your couple goals while you’re existing on the surface of what it really takes to be ALL IN with your significant other. @philheath and I have never once commented “couple goals” on anyone’s photo as we know the level of hard work that it takes to stay together in a wicked world. So when you see us and say couple goals, I want you to see this…

A lot of SIN.
A relationship started by sex/ lust first.
Zero Trust and very little Respect/Self Respect.
Two broken & divorced hearts.
Losing nearly everything. 
Being divided by the weight of the World.
Being saved as a couple by the Lords Grace and Mercy. 
Working daily to live life in accordance to the lord. 
A lot of failing forward.
Years of Adversity. 
Years of long arguments and finding new ways to communicate.
Experiencing “Through Sickness and Health”
A lot of compassion.
A lot of unconditional love.
Finally connecting on the physical level with the intention to build.

🤷🏻‍♀️AND WE STILL HAVEN’T MASTERED ANY OF IT! 

It’s rare you find your soulmate, @philheath and I can honestly say we have that with one another. It took a lot of struggle to get here and stand together as a Unit. If that is couple goals to you, then you’ve arrived, you deserve to find your soul mate. This isn’t easy and I wouldn’t want it any other way. We owe it all to God and our Champion Spirits🙏

Love you Phillip @philheath

node.text:
I haven't been this excited in awhile. 

Reason: it's my Queen @shuriecremona Birthday!

Been together for 6yrs and it's been one helluva ride and cannot hold my excitement, as Shurie continues to impress me with her strength, intellect, perseverance and compassion! 

The love that you provide me far exceeds my expectations and although I can be a stubborn Bull sometimes, you're truly the only one who can bring me back on track. Through the million miles we have flown together, countless hours spent together in hotels, trains and of course gyms, you have always been my goto, my best friend and lover. 

Thank you for continuing onward when adversity hits, providing even Me levels of encouragement when others simply couldn't. You know the real Phillip and I'm blessed to know you too. 

Thank you Shurie for understanding me, always loving me even when I doubted and at times didn't love myself enough. 

May your birthday be fueled with love, positivity, peace and momentum into the days, months ahead as you're transitioning into a whole new world filled with endless possibilities. 

Overall, thank you for being YOU!!!

Love you with everything I got gorgeous!!!

Happy Birthday!!!

node.text:
A #flashbackfriday when @shuriecremona and I attended a UFC in San Diego back in 2015 where @thefrankmir and @hollyholm dominated their opponents. What's wild is I remember watching Holly Holm and telling Shurie, "she's gonna beat Rhonda, you watch" and in her next fight she did just that, creating one of the largest upsets we had ever seen at that time. 

Can't wait for Shurie and I to get back out to concerts and sporting events as it was something we did often while dating. 

Anyway, I hope you are all finishing this week up stronger than the hair on my head back then lol. Yes I can still grow it, I just hate waiting at barbershops. 

Train hard, train smart and of course HAVE FUN!!!!
